---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

// Pricing model ratified 2026-05-16 in docs/specs/pricing.md §5.5.4.
// Price points are still deferred to first-buyer triangulation; this page
// names the model shape and the billing surfaces that shipped in Wave 15.

const tiers = [
  {
    label: "Metis Community",
    price: "$0",
    kicker: "open-core gateway",
    body: "Self-host the gateway, agent loop, canonical IR, routing engine, trace store, pattern store, heuristic evaluator, and deployment-level analytics. BYO provider keys and infra.",
    cta: "start free",
  },
  {
    label: "Metis Pro",
    price: "per active seat",
    kicker: "team deployment",
    body: "Per active user per month. Adds full multi-user identity, per-team caps, per-user/team analytics, LLM judge tier, audit export, hosted operations, and the agent upgrade path.",
    cta: "talk pricing",
  },
  {
    label: "Metis Enterprise",
    price: "custom",
    kicker: "outcome-linked",
    body: "Pro plus a capped percent-of-savings add-on for procurement-led buyers, custom routing policies, longer audit retention, deployment support, and dedicated success engineering.",
    cta: "talk to us",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Pricing | Metis by 2sum AI"
  description="Pricing for Metis from 2sum AI — open-core gateway, per-seat Pro, and Enterprise savings add-on."
>
  <div
    class="pointer-events-none fixed inset-0 grid-bg opacity-60 [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black_30%,transparent_75%)]"
  >
  </div>

  <div class="relative">
    <Nav current="pricing" />

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pb-12 pt-20">
      <div
        class="mb-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-accent/40 bg-bg-card px-3 py-1 text-xs"
      >
        <span class="relative flex h-2 w-2">
          <span
            class="absolute inline-flex h-full w-full animate-ping rounded-full bg-accent opacity-50"
          ></span>
          <span
            class="relative inline-flex h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-accent"
          ></span>
        </span>
        <span class="text-accent">model ratified &middot; billing module shipped</span>
      </div>

      <h1
        class="max-w-4xl text-3xl font-bold leading-[1.15] tracking-tight sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl"
      >
        Pricing.
      </h1>
      <p
        class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-muted sm:text-lg"
      >
        The model is now fixed: open-core gateway, per-seat Pro, and a
        reserved Enterprise savings add-on. Price points stay commercial,
        but the shape is no longer TBD. Metis never resells provider tokens;
        you bring your Anthropic / OpenAI / OpenRouter keys.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <a
          href="/signup"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded border border-accent bg-accent px-5 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-bg transition-colors hover:bg-accent/90"
        >
          discuss a Pro pilot
          <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TIER GRID -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pb-20">
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        {
          tiers.map((tier) => (
            <div class="flex flex-col rounded-lg border border-border bg-bg-card p-6">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-accent">
                {tier.label}
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-fg-muted">{tier.kicker}</p>
              <p class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                {tier.price}
              </p>
              <p class="mt-3 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
                {tier.body}
              </p>
              <div class="mt-6">
                <a
                  href="/signup"
                  class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded border border-border-strong bg-bg px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold text-fg transition-colors hover:border-accent"
                >
                  {tier.cta}
                  <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>

      <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-fg-dim">
        Model shape ratified in docs/specs/pricing.md §5.5.4 and implemented
        in Wave 15's opt-in billing module. Dollar price points remain deferred
        to first-buyer triangulation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="border-t border-border bg-bg-elev/40">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
          Questions we keep getting.
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-fg">
              Will the Community gateway stay free?
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-fg-muted">
              Yes. The gateway, the agent loop, the canonical IR, the
              routing engine, the trace store, the pattern store, and
              the evaluator are in the $0 self-hosted Community path.
              License text stays owner-side; we never see your traffic.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-fg">
              What's in the paid tiers, then?
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-fg-muted">
              A managed control plane: hosted gateway, multi-team
              rollups, SSO, longer audit-log retention, the pattern
              store as a service, custom evaluator rubrics, support
              SLAs, and an enterprise %-of-savings add-on for buyers
              who want their bill tied to the savings curve.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-fg">
              What shipped in billing?
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-fg-muted">
              Stripe-backed subscription lifecycle, webhook idempotency,
              Pro per-seat lines, Enterprise savings usage records, six
              billing audit events, and tier-axis quota composition. Billing
              is opt-in via deployment config; deployments without it are
              byte-for-byte free-tier runtime.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-fg">
              Does Enterprise mean Metis takes a cut of provider spend?
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-fg-muted">
              No. The Enterprise add-on meters verified savings, not raw
              tokens. Provider invoices still come from the provider. The
              savings line is reserved for buyers who want an outcome-linked
              contract on top of the predictable Pro seat floor.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="border-t border-border">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
          Start free. Convert when the team needs controls.
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl text-fg-muted">
          Community is the zero-friction gateway. Pro starts when identity,
          hard caps, audit export, hosted operations, and the agent matter.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <a
            href="/signup"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded border border-accent bg-accent px-5 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-bg transition-colors hover:bg-accent/90"
          >
            sign up
            <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
